cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the analysis of temporal patterns in ambulance call activity and the use of location intelligence data to predict health risks in a geographic area. This work involves the use of machine learning techniques and data analysis, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper deals with healthcare policy design, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). The use of location intelligence data and online platforms to predict epidemiological trends also falls under the sub-categories of cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
